Class Driver

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.model.DriverBase
      • net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.model.Driver

  • public final class Driver
extends DriverBase
    Represents a model of a driver with their track overrides included as described by AMS2 Developers here: Reiza AMS2Forums Stores Livery Name that is shared with its track specific overrides.

      • liveryName

        private final javafx.beans.property.StringProperty liveryName
        In game name of the livery. Ths value determines to which car the custom AI values are going to be applied.

      • trackOverrides

        private final javafx.collections.ObservableList<TrackOverride> trackOverrides
        List of all track specific overrides that this driver has. Track specific overrides are applied on specific tracks and can override a variety of different values including a driver's name.
